.SH "NAME"
systemd-ask-password-console.service, systemd-ask-password-console.path, systemd-ask-password-wall.service, systemd-ask-password-wall.path \- Query tha user fo' system passwordz on tha console n' via wall
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.PP
systemd\-ask\-password\-console\&.service
.PP
systemd\-ask\-password\-console\&.path
.PP
systemd\-ask\-password\-wall\&.service
.PP
systemd\-ask\-password\-wall\&.path
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
systemd\-ask\-password\-console\&.service
is a system steez dat queries tha user fo' system passwordz (like fuckin hard disk encryption keys n' SSL certificate passphrases) on tha console\&. Well shiiiit, it is intended ta be used durin boot ta ensure proper handlin of passwordz necessary fo' boot\&.
systemd\-ask\-password\-wall\&.service
is a system steez dat informs all logged up in playas fo' system passwordz via
\fBwall\fR(1)\&. Well shiiiit, it is intended ta be used afta boot ta ensure dat playas is properly notified\&.
.PP
See the
\m[blue]\fBdeveloper documentation\fR\m[]\&\s-2\u[1]\d\s+2
for mo' shiznit bout tha system password logic\&.
.PP
Note dat these skillz invoke
\fBsystemd-tty-ask-password-agent\fR(1)
with either the
\fB\-\-watch \-\-console\fR
or
\fB\-\-watch \-\-wall\fR
command line parameters\&.
